net.wombatrpgs.rainfall.maps
Class MapObject

java.lang.Object
  net.wombatrpgs.rainfall.maps.MapObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<MapObject>, Renderable, Positionable, PositionSetable
Direct Known Subclasses:
MapEvent
public abstract class MapObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements Renderable, PositionSetable, java.lang.Comparable<MapObject>

All objects that appear in Tiled maps that are not tiles extend this class. This includes both characters and events.

getHitbox

public abstract Hitbox getHitbox()
Gets the hitbox associated with this map object at this point in time. It's abstract so that events with different animations can return the appropriate object for each call.

Returns:
The hitbox being used at the moment, never null

onCollide

public abstract void onCollide(MapObject other,
                               CollisionResult result)
Called when this object is colliding with another event in the wild. If this is true, unless you move out of collision, it'll be called every frame. So if you want to have a hitbox but not be a physical entity really, then don't respond to this method. There should be some sort of double dispatch here really. Maybe.

Parameters:
other - The other object involved in the collision
result - Info about the collision

isOverlappingAllowed

public abstract boolean isOverlappingAllowed()
Determine whether overlapping with this object in general is allowed. This is sort of a physicsy thing. Allowing it implies no physical presence on the map, even if this object has a hitbox. Disallowing it is usually a signal that collisions need to be resolvled.

Returns:
True if overlapping with this object is okay
